{"unit_id": "u0001", "document_id": "hydra-settlement-test-fixture-4edb3c3c", "source_file": "C:\\agentictrading\\tests\\fixtures\\hydra-settlement-test-fixture.pdf", "page": 1, "section_path": [], "bbox": {"l": 78.0, "t": 708.924, "r": 533.0939999999999, "b": 670.274, "coord_origin": "BOTTOMLEFT"}, "content_hash": "sha256:fb3859b38ae41aa3", "extraction_method": "docling", "confidence": 1.0, "unit_type": "heading", "text": "Hydra Settlement: A Synchronous Layer-2 for eUTXO Chains"}
{"unit_id": "u0002", "document_id": "hydra-settlement-test-fixture-4edb3c3c", "source_file": "C:\\agentictrading\\tests\\fixtures\\hydra-settlement-test-fixture.pdf", "page": 1, "section_path": ["Hydra Settlement: A Synchronous Layer-2 for eUTXO Chains"], "bbox": {"l": 78.0, "t": 655.18, "r": 235.83, "b": 645.93, "coord_origin": "BOTTOMLEFT"}, "content_hash": "sha256:f87f30c0a4cf7971", "extraction_method": "docling", "confidence": 1.0, "unit_type": "paragraph", "text": "Working Paper, Test Fixture Edition"}
{"unit_id": "u0003", "document_id": "hydra-settlement-test-fixture-4edb3c3c", "source_file": "C:\\agentictrading\\tests\\fixtures\\hydra-settlement-test-fixture.pdf", "page": 1, "section_path": [], "bbox": {"l": 78.0, "t": 619.324, "r": 203.01000000000002, "b": 602.674, "coord_origin": "BOTTOMLEFT"}, "content_hash": "sha256:6e62ee82e3df2a7d", "extraction_method": "docling", "confidence": 1.0, "unit_type": "heading", "text": "1. Introduction"}
{"unit_id": "u0004", "document_id": "hydra-settlement-test-fixture-4edb3c3c", "source_file": "C:\\agentictrading\\tests\\fixtures\\hydra-settlement-test-fixture.pdf", "page": 1, "section_path": ["1. Introduction"], "bbox": {"l": 78.0, "t": 587.5799999999999, "r": 520.94, "b": 542.3299999999999, "coord_origin": "BOTTOMLEFT"}, "content_hash": "sha256:feb547bf78a07292", "extraction_method": "docling", "confidence": 1.0, "unit_type": "paragraph", "text": "Hydra is a family of Layer-2 protocols designed to scale Cardano-style eUTXO ledgers by allowing a small set of participants to run an isolated, high-throughput state channel called a Hydra Head. Transactions inside a Head settle instantly among participants and are only reconciled with the main chain when the Head is closed."}
{"unit_id": "u0005", "document_id": "hydra-settlement-test-fixture-4edb3c3c", "source_file": "C:\\agentictrading\\tests\\fixtures\\hydra-settlement-test-fixture.pdf", "page": 1, "section_path": [], "bbox": {"l": 78.0, "t": 522.924, "r": 204.036, "b": 506.274, "coord_origin": "BOTTOMLEFT"}, "content_hash": "sha256:d6af9ee2c5a6f556", "extraction_method": "docling", "confidence": 1.0, "unit_type": "heading", "text": "2. Architecture"}
{"unit_id": "u0006", "document_id": "hydra-settlement-test-fixture-4edb3c3c", "source_file": "C:\\agentictrading\\tests\\fixtures\\hydra-settlement-test-fixture.pdf", "page": 1, "section_path": ["2. Architecture"], "bbox": {"l": 78.0, "t": 490.052, "r": 199.39400000000003, "b": 477.102, "coord_origin": "BOTTOMLEFT"}, "content_hash": "sha256:97f41e6914bd936a", "extraction_method": "docling", "confidence": 1.0, "unit_type": "heading", "text": "2.1 Head Lifecycle"}
{"unit_id": "u0007", "document_id": "hydra-settlement-test-fixture-4edb3c3c", "source_file": "C:\\agentictrading\\tests\\fixtures\\hydra-settlement-test-fixture.pdf", "page": 1, "section_path": ["2. Architecture", "2.1 Head Lifecycle"], "bbox": {"l": 78.0, "t": 465.18, "r": 525.9599999999998, "b": 419.93, "coord_origin": "BOTTOMLEFT"}, "content_hash": "sha256:b6c8bc565245a9d0", "extraction_method": "docling", "confidence": 1.0, "unit_type": "paragraph", "text": "A Hydra Head moves through four phases: Init, Open, Close, and Fanout. During Init, participants commit UTXOs from the main chain. During Open, participants exchange signed snapshots off-chain. Close posts the latest snapshot on-chain, and Fanout distributes the final UTXO set back to the main ledger."}
{"unit_id": "u0008", "document_id": "hydra-settlement-test-fixture-4edb3c3c", "source_file": "C:\\agentictrading\\tests\\fixtures\\hydra-settlement-test-fixture.pdf", "page": 1, "section_path": ["2. Architecture"], "bbox": {"l": 78.0, "t": 393.252, "r": 253.84, "b": 380.30199999999996, "coord_origin": "BOTTOMLEFT"}, "content_hash": "sha256:2cbcc3d0c1fd422d", "extraction_method": "docling", "confidence": 1.0, "unit_type": "heading", "text": "2.2 Settlement Guarantees"}
{"unit_id": "u0009", "document_id": "hydra-settlement-test-fixture-4edb3c3c", "source_file": "C:\\agentictrading\\tests\\fixtures\\hydra-settlement-test-fixture.pdf", "page": 1, "section_path": ["2. Architecture", "2.2 Settlement Guarantees"], "bbox": {"l": 78.0, "t": 368.38, "r": 515.9599999999999, "b": 335.13, "coord_origin": "BOTTOMLEFT"}, "content_hash": "sha256:6c3a286307040c3b", "extraction_method": "docling", "confidence": 1.0, "unit_type": "paragraph", "text": "Because every state transition inside the Head requires unanimous signatures from all participants, Hydra can be used as a synchronous settlement layer over Cardano-style eUTXO state: once all parties sign a snapshot, that state is final among them even before it touches the main chain."}
{"unit_id": "u0010", "document_id": "hydra-settlement-test-fixture-4edb3c3c", "source_file": "C:\\agentictrading\\tests\\fixtures\\hydra-settlement-test-fixture.pdf", "page": 1, "section_path": [], "bbox": {"l": 78.0, "t": 315.724, "r": 309.01200000000006, "b": 299.074, "coord_origin": "BOTTOMLEFT"}, "content_hash": "sha256:3aecc613f00a71db", "extraction_method": "docling", "confidence": 1.0, "unit_type": "heading", "text": "3. Throughput Comparison"}
{"unit_id": "u0011", "document_id": "hydra-settlement-test-fixture-4edb3c3c", "source_file": "C:\\agentictrading\\tests\\fixtures\\hydra-settlement-test-fixture.pdf", "page": 1, "section_path": ["3. Throughput Comparison"], "bbox": {"l": 78.0, "t": 283.98, "r": 500.97999999999985, "b": 262.73, "coord_origin": "BOTTOMLEFT"}, "content_hash": "sha256:61715c09836d8f55", "extraction_method": "docling", "confidence": 1.0, "unit_type": "paragraph", "text": "The table below compares theoretical transaction throughput across configurations tested in the reference implementation."}
{"unit_id": "u0012", "document_id": "hydra-settlement-test-fixture-4edb3c3c", "source_file": "C:\\agentictrading\\tests\\fixtures\\hydra-settlement-test-fixture.pdf", "page": 1, "section_path": ["3. Throughput Comparison"], "bbox": {"l": 132.12965393066406, "t": 253.138427734375, "r": 479.43280029296875, "b": 179.51373291015625, "coord_origin": "BOTTOMLEFT"}, "content_hash": "sha256:acafa0000bc9b5dc", "extraction_method": "docling", "confidence": 1.0, "unit_type": "table", "text": "Configuration | Participants | TPS | Finality\nBaseline L1 | - | 250 | ~20s\nHydra Head (small) | 3 | 1,000 | <1s\nHydra Head (large) | 10 | 800 | <1s"}
{"unit_id": "u0013", "document_id": "hydra-settlement-test-fixture-4edb3c3c", "source_file": "C:\\agentictrading\\tests\\fixtures\\hydra-settlement-test-fixture.pdf", "page": 2, "section_path": [], "bbox": {"l": 78.0, "t": 708.924, "r": 210.03, "b": 692.274, "coord_origin": "BOTTOMLEFT"}, "content_hash": "sha256:92d0706627773d93", "extraction_method": "docling", "confidence": 1.0, "unit_type": "heading", "text": "4. Threat Model"}
{"unit_id": "u0014", "document_id": "hydra-settlement-test-fixture-4edb3c3c", "source_file": "C:\\agentictrading\\tests\\fixtures\\hydra-settlement-test-fixture.pdf", "page": 2, "section_path": ["4. Threat Model"], "bbox": {"l": 78.0, "t": 677.18, "r": 509.87, "b": 643.93, "coord_origin": "BOTTOMLEFT"}, "content_hash": "sha256:da52e1e0c7073e68", "extraction_method": "docling", "confidence": 1.0, "unit_type": "paragraph", "text": "Hydra Heads assume an honest majority is not required; instead, safety relies on unanimity and a contestation period during Close. If a participant posts a stale snapshot, any other participant can contest it on-chain within the contestation window by presenting a newer, validly signed snapshot."}
{"unit_id": "u0015", "document_id": "hydra-settlement-test-fixture-4edb3c3c", "source_file": "C:\\agentictrading\\tests\\fixtures\\hydra-settlement-test-fixture.pdf", "page": 2, "section_path": [], "bbox": {"l": 78.0, "t": 624.524, "r": 237.048, "b": 607.874, "coord_origin": "BOTTOMLEFT"}, "content_hash": "sha256:a09fe841e33c3ec6", "extraction_method": "docling", "confidence": 1.0, "unit_type": "heading", "text": "5. Open Questions"}
{"unit_id": "u0016", "document_id": "hydra-settlement-test-fixture-4edb3c3c", "source_file": "C:\\agentictrading\\tests\\fixtures\\hydra-settlement-test-fixture.pdf", "page": 2, "section_path": ["5. Open Questions"], "bbox": {"l": 78.0, "t": 592.78, "r": 515.9799999999998, "b": 559.53, "coord_origin": "BOTTOMLEFT"}, "content_hash": "sha256:a147c4f2faa61df5", "extraction_method": "docling", "confidence": 1.0, "unit_type": "paragraph", "text": "It remains an open question how Hydra Heads compose with external delegated-signing standards such as the Open Wallet Standard (OWS), particularly when an autonomous agent - rather than a human participant - holds one of the Head's signing keys."}
{"unit_id": "u0017", "document_id": "hydra-settlement-test-fixture-4edb3c3c", "source_file": "C:\\agentictrading\\tests\\fixtures\\hydra-settlement-test-fixture.pdf", "page": 2, "section_path": ["5. Open Questions"], "bbox": {"l": 78.0, "t": 536.38, "r": 246.95000000000007, "b": 527.13, "coord_origin": "BOTTOMLEFT"}, "content_hash": "sha256:691f411127c1125e", "extraction_method": "docling", "confidence": 1.0, "unit_type": "caption", "text": "Figure 1: Head Lifecycle (placeholder)"}
